2172.subject: ENSTU
2172.descrlong:
This Service Learning course addresses strategies for supporting equitable formal and informal educational opportunities and access to healthy natural environments for all, regardless of their cultural, linguistic, or economic background. Service learning placements in schools and other agencies help students deepen their understanding of basic biology principles and methodologies for facilitating learning by diverse students and community members. 

(Prereq: (Junior or Senior Standing) and (GE Areas A1 and A2 and A3 and B2)
